Sunshine Key trailer park		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Man drying hair at campsite in Sunshine Key		Carlebach, Michael L.			Written on slide: "Man drying his hair-Sunshine Key"; Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Reflection of sun on Sunshine Key mangroves		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Sunshine Key mangrove swamp		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Resident walking dogs at Sunshine Key trailer park		Carlebach, Michael L.			Written on slide: "Sunshine Key"; Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Dump station sign on Sunshine Key trailer park		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Reflection of sun on Sunshine Key mangroves		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park. Sunshine Key mangroves		Carlebach, Michael L.			Ohio Key was a small mangrove-covered island between Key West and Key Largo.  The island retained a community of buttonwood, mangroves, and salt ponds to about 1970. Between 1970 and 1973, its name was changed to "Sunshine Key" and changed the northern half of the island into a land fill for a travel trailer park.
